1856f4b3 [simon@midnightblue] vic20 set text color
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #On the VIC-20, you have a few options to set text color:
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #• Using POKE to color memory* (most common):
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #POKE 38400 + X, C
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #Where `X` is the screen position (0-505) and `C` is the color code (0-7):
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #- 0 = Black
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #- 1 = White
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #- 2 = Red
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #- 3 = Cyan
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #- 4 = Purple
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #- 5 = Green
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #- 6 = Blue
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #- 7 = Yellow
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #• Setting color for current position*:
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #POKE 646, C: PRINT "HELLO"
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #• Control characters* (CHR$ codes 1-8 for colors):
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #PRINT CHR$(5);"GREEN TEXT"
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #• At specific screen location*:
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #POKE 7680 + Y * 22 + X, ASC("A"): POKE 38400 + Y * 22 + X, 2
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #(7680/1E00 is screen memory, 38400/9600 is color memory, 22 columns wide)
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #Want a specific example or need to set border/background colors too?
1856f549 [kimi-k2.5] #
