1857918f [simon@midnightblue] assemblers for the vic20
185792a4 [kimi-k2.5] #• Native VIC-20 Assemblers* (run on the hardware)
185792a4 [kimi-k2.5] #- VICMON – The classic monitor/assembler cartridge from Commodore. POKEs, machine code,
185792a4 [kimi-k2.5] #basic assembly
185792a4 [kimi-k2.5] #- PAL / VIC-PAL – Popular full-featured assembler, often used with the Super Expander
185792a4 [kimi-k2.5] #- MAE (Macro Assembler Editor) – Powerful, later era
185792a4 [kimi-k2.5] #- Merlin – Well-regarded, ported from Apple II
185792a4 [kimi-k2.5] #- Famous Assembler – German, quite capable
185792a4 [kimi-k2.5] #
185792a4 [kimi-k2.5] #• Modern Cross-Assemblers* (build on PC, output .prg)
185792a4 [kimi-k2.5] #- ACME – Very popular, clean syntax, good VIC-20 support
185792a4 [kimi-k2.5] #- Kick Assembler – Java-based, modern features, macros
185792a4 [kimi-k2.5] #- TMPx – Portable, stable
185792a4 [kimi-k2.5] #- xa (André Fachat's) – Portable, unix-friendly
185792a4 [kimi-k2.5] #- DASM – Classic, multi-platform
185792a4 [kimi-k2.5] #- ca65 (cc65 suite) – Powerful macro assembler, linker support
185792a4 [kimi-k2.5] #
185792a4 [kimi-k2.5] #• IDEs*
185792a4 [kimi-k2.5] #- CBM prg Studio – Windows IDE with built-in assembler and emulator integration
185792a4 [kimi-k2.5] #- Relaunch64 – Java IDE for C64/VIC cross-dev
185792a4 [kimi-k2.5] #- VS Code – Extensions for ACME, KickAss syntax highlighting
185792a4 [kimi-k2.5] #
185792a4 [kimi-k2.5] #Most output standard `.prg` files (load address 1001 for BASIC stub, or 1000 for auto-run ML).
185792a4 [kimi-k2.5] #VIC-20 memory map is tricky—use `=1001` or `=1200`+ to avoid BASIC/ZP.
185792a4 [kimi-k2.5] #
185792a4 [kimi-k2.5] #Preference? ACME or Kick Assembler are solid modern choices.
185792a4 [kimi-k2.5] #
