1857d5cb [simon@midnightblue] memory map of vic20 when 16K expansion connected
1857d707 [kimi-k2.5] #VIC-20 Memory Map with 16K Expansion (typically mapped at 2000-5FFF):
1857d707 [kimi-k2.5] #
1857d707 [kimi-k2.5] #
1857d707 [kimi-k2.5] #$0000-$03FF  1KB  System RAM (zero page, stack, screen)
1857d707 [kimi-k2.5] #$0400-$0FFF  3KB  Reserved/unused or 3K expansion if installed
1857d707 [kimi-k2.5] #$1000-$1FFF  4KB  User BASIC RAM / Screen memory
1857d707 [kimi-k2.5] #$2000-$3FFF  8KB  16K Expansion Block 1
1857d707 [kimi-k2.5] #$4000-$5FFF  8KB  16K Expansion Block 2
1857d707 [kimi-k2.5] #$6000-$7FFF  8KB  Free for cartridges/ROM
1857d707 [kimi-k2.5] #$8000-$8FFF  4KB  Character ROM
1857d707 [kimi-k2.5] #$9000-$900F       VIC-I Video registers
1857d707 [kimi-k2.5] #$9110-$911F       VIA 1 (6522 I/O)
1857d707 [kimi-k2.5] #$9120-$912F       VIA 2 (6522 I/O)
1857d707 [kimi-k2.5] #$9400-$97FF  1KB  Color RAM (nibble-wide)
1857d707 [kimi-k2.5] #$9800-$9FFF  2KB  Reserved/unused
1857d707 [kimi-k2.5] #$A000-$BFFF  8KB  Cartridge ROM / RAM or free
1857d707 [kimi-k2.5] #$C000-$DFFF  8KB  BASIC ROM
1857d707 [kimi-k2.5] #$E000-$FFFF  8KB  KERNAL ROM
1857d707 [kimi-k2.5] #
1857d707 [kimi-k2.5] #
1857d707 [kimi-k2.5] #Total RAM: 1K (base) + 4K (base) + 16K (expansion) = 21KB available to BASIC/user.
1857d707 [kimi-k2.5] #
1857d707 [kimi-k2.5] #The 16K expansion is typically contiguous from 2000-5FFF, giving BASIC programs significantly more
1857d707 [kimi-k2.5] #memory (user BASIC starts at 1200 with screen at 1E00).
1857d707 [kimi-k2.5] #
