193ab174 [simon@midnightblue] interrupt vectors and 6502 pins
193ab207 [deepseek-chat] #The 6502 microprocessor has 40 pins, including:
193ab207 [deepseek-chat] #
193ab207 [deepseek-chat] #- Address bus (16 pins: A0-A15)
193ab207 [deepseek-chat] #- Data bus (8 pins: D0-D7)
193ab207 [deepseek-chat] #- Control pins: RDY, IRQ, NMI, RES, SO, SYNC, R/W, Φ0, Φ1, Φ2
193ab207 [deepseek-chat] #- Power: Vss (GND), Vcc (+5V)
193ab207 [deepseek-chat] #
193ab207 [deepseek-chat] #• Interrupt vectors* (stored at fixed memory locations):
193ab207 [deepseek-chat] #- FFFA-FFFB: NMI (Non-Maskable Interrupt)
193ab207 [deepseek-chat] #- FFFC-FFFD: RESET
193ab207 [deepseek-chat] #- FFFE-FFFF: IRQ/BRK (Maskable Interrupt)
193ab207 [deepseek-chat] #
193ab207 [deepseek-chat] #NMI is edge-triggered and cannot be disabled. IRQ can be masked using the I flag.
193ab207 [deepseek-chat] #
