1a7b5b20 [gemini-3.1-pro] #Currently, the `vblank` loop sets the pin to High-Z (black level) and holds it there for 25 entire
1a7b5b20 [gemini-3.1-pro] #lines (72,000 cycles). Standard PAL requires uninterrupted synchronization pulses during the
1a7b5b20 [gemini-3.1-pro] #vertical blanking interval (specifically, a sequence of pre-equalizing pulses, broad vertical sync
1a7b5b21 [gemini-3.1-pro] #pulses, and post-equalizing pulses).
