1a7b65d9 [simon@midnightblue] can you explain how the color burst signal works and general order of hsync pporces and active line
1a7b6711 [gemini-3.1-pro] #Here is the general sequence of a single horizontal video line and how the color burst fits into
1a7b6711 [gemini-3.1-pro] #it.
1a7b6712 [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1a7b6712 [gemini-3.1-pro] #• Horizontal Line Sequence*
1a7b6712 [gemini-3.1-pro] #A standard horizontal scan line operates in a continuous cycle, typically measured starting from
1a7b6712 [gemini-3.1-pro] #the sync pulse:
1a7b6712 [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1a7b6712 [gemini-3.1-pro] #1. Horizontal Sync (H-Sync): A pulse driven below the black level (sync tip) that triggers
1a7b6712 [gemini-3.1-pro] #the display to return the electron beam (or digital equivalent) to the left side of the screen.
1a7b6712 [gemini-3.1-pro] #2. Back Porch: A short period held at the black blanking level immediately following the
1a7b6712 [gemini-3.1-pro] #H-Sync. This allows the display hardware time to settle after the horizontal retrace.
1a7b6712 [gemini-3.1-pro] #3. Active Video: The visible portion of the line where the luminance (brightness) and
1a7b6712 [gemini-3.1-pro] #chrominance (color) signals are drawn.
1a7b6712 [gemini-3.1-pro] #4. Front Porch: A brief blanking period at the black level after the active video ends. It
1a7b6712 [gemini-3.1-pro] #provides a buffer before the next H-Sync pulse drops, ensuring the video signal is completely off.
1a7b6712 [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1a7b6712 [gemini-3.1-pro] #• The Color Burst Signal*
1a7b6712 [gemini-3.1-pro] #The color burst is a synchronization reference placed directly on the Back Porch.
1a7b6712 [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1a7b6712 [gemini-3.1-pro] #• What it is: A short, unmodulated burst of the color subcarrier sine wave. For PAL, this
1a7b6712 [gemini-3.1-pro] #is exactly 10 cycles at 4.43361875 MHz.
1a7b6712 [gemini-3.1-pro] #• Purpose: Color in composite video is encoded using phase and amplitude modulation. To
1a7b6712 [gemini-3.1-pro] #decode the exact hues, the TV needs a precise reference point. The burst synchronizes the TV's
1a7b6712 [gemini-3.1-pro] #internal color oscillator to the exact frequency and phase of the broadcast signal.
1a7b6712 [gemini-3.1-pro] #• PAL Specifics: PAL stands for "Phase Alternating Line." To correct for transmission phase
1a7b6712 [gemini-3.1-pro] #errors (which cause color tint shifts in NTSC), the phase of the PAL color burst swings between
1a7b6713 [gemini-3.1-pro] #+135° and -135° on alternating lines. The TV averages consecutive lines to cancel out any color
1a7b6713 [gemini-3.1-pro] #distortion.
1a7b6713 [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1a7b6713 [gemini-3.1-pro] #Generating a precise 4.43 MHz color burst via PIO requires very careful clock division, as the
1a7b6713 [gemini-3.1-pro] #subcarrier frequency must be highly accurate for the TV to lock onto the color.
1a7b6713 [gemini-3.1-pro] #
