1a7b7427 [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1a7b7427 [gemini-3.1-pro] #1. The Color Burst Signal
1a7b7427 [gemini-3.1-pro] #The color burst is a short, precise high-frequency sine wave (4.43361875 MHz for PAL) transmitted
1a7b7427 [gemini-3.1-pro] #during the back porch of every horizontal line.
1a7b7427 [gemini-3.1-pro] #• Purpose: It serves as a frequency and phase reference clock for the television's color
1a7b7427 [gemini-3.1-pro] #decoder. The TV uses this to decode the color (chrominance) information superimposed on the active
1a7b7427 [gemini-3.1-pro] #video signal.
1a7b7427 [gemini-3.1-pro] #• PAL Specifics: In PAL (Phase Alternating Line), the phase of the color burst alternates
1a7b7427 [gemini-3.1-pro] #by 90 degrees (+135° and -135°) on each consecutive scanline. This allows the TV to automatically
1a7b7427 [gemini-3.1-pro] #cancel out color phase errors (hue shifts) during transmission.
1a7b7427 [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1a7b7427 [gemini-3.1-pro] #2. General Order of a Horizontal Line
1a7b7427 [gemini-3.1-pro] #A single horizontal scanline progresses in the following order:
1a7b7427 [gemini-3.1-pro] #1.  Front Porch: A brief period at the blanking voltage level (~0.3V). It provides a buffer
1a7b7427 [gemini-3.1-pro] #between the active video and the sync pulse.
1a7b7427 [gemini-3.1-pro] #2.  Horizontal Sync (HSync): A pulse driven to the lowest voltage level (0V). This tells
1a7b7427 [gemini-3.1-pro] #the electron gun (or digital scaler) to return to the left side of the screen.
1a7b7427 [gemini-3.1-pro] #3.  Back Porch: A return to the blanking voltage level (~0.3V). The color burst is
1a7b7427 [gemini-3.1-pro] #transmitted here.
1a7b7427 [gemini-3.1-pro] #4.  Active Video: The actual picture data, varying between black (~0.3V) and peak white
1a7b7427 [gemini-3.1-pro] #(~1.0V).
1a7b7427 [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1a7b7427 [gemini-3.1-pro] #3. RP2350 Components for Video Generation
1a7b7427 [gemini-3.1-pro] #Beyond the PIO you are currently utilizing, the RP2350 has several hardware features highly suited
1a7b7427 [gemini-3.1-pro] #for video generation:
1a7b7428 [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1a7b7428 [gemini-3.1-pro] #• HSTX (High-Speed Transmission): This is a new peripheral specific to the RP2350. It is
1a7b7428 [gemini-3.1-pro] #designed specifically for continuous, high-bandwidth data streams like DVI, HDMI, or high-speed
1a7b7428 [gemini-3.1-pro] #DACs. It handles data shifting and clocking automatically, potentially freeing up PIO state
1a7b7428 [gemini-3.1-pro] #machines.
1a7b7428 [gemini-3.1-pro] #• DMA (Direct Memory Access): Essential for moving pixel data from RAM to the PIO (or HSTX)
1a7b7428 [gemini-3.1-pro] #buffers automatically. This allows the CPU to focus entirely on game logic or rendering the next
1a7b7428 [gemini-3.1-pro] #frame without managing the strict timing of the active video line.
1a7b7428 [gemini-3.1-pro] #• SIO Interpolators: These can be very useful for fast texture mapping, scaling, or
1a7b7428 [gemini-3.1-pro] #unpacking compressed pixel formats on the fly before sending them to the DMA/PIO.
1a7b7428 [gemini-3.1-pro] #
