1a84e272 [deepseek-chat] #• Memory organization:*
1a84e272 [deepseek-chat] #- 264KB SRAM - Contiguous address space
1a84e272 [deepseek-chat] #- 8KB ROM - Bootrom with utility functions
1a84e272 [deepseek-chat] #- DMA can access all SRAM equally
1a84e272 [deepseek-chat] #
1a84e272 [deepseek-chat] #• Optimization strategies:*
1a84e272 [deepseek-chat] #
1a84e272 [deepseek-chat] #• 1. Cache-friendly layout:*
1a84e272 [deepseek-chat] #- Place frequently accessed data together
1a84e273 [deepseek-chat] #- DMA buffers aligned to cache lines (32 bytes)
1a84e273 [deepseek-chat] #
1a84e273 [deepseek-chat] #• 2. DMA-efficient patterns:*
1a84e273 [deepseek-chat] #- Align buffers to 32-bit boundaries (DMA requirement)
1a84e273 [deepseek-chat] #- Place buffers in different cache ways to reduce contention
1a84e273 [deepseek-chat] #
1a84e273 [deepseek-chat] #• 3. SRAM partitioning (manual):*
1a84e273 [deepseek-chat] #
1a84e273 [deepseek-chat] #// Example manual partitioning
1a84e273 [deepseek-chat] ##define VIDEO_BUF_START  0x20000000
1a84e273 [deepseek-chat] ##define AUDIO_BUF_START  0x20010000
1a84e273 [deepseek-chat] ##define DATA_BUF_START   0x20020000
1a84e273 [deepseek-chat] #
1a84e273 [deepseek-chat] #
1a84e273 [deepseek-chat] #• 4. Cache considerations:*
1a84e273 [deepseek-chat] #- RP2350 has 16KB cache (2-way set associative)
1a84e273 [deepseek-chat] #- DMA bypasses cache (unless using XIP flash)
1a84e273 [deepseek-chat] #- Consider cache aliasing if buffers share cache sets
1a84e273 [deepseek-chat] #
1a84e273 [deepseek-chat] #• 5. DMA priority:*
1a84e273 [deepseek-chat] #- 12 channels with configurable priority
1a84e273 [deepseek-chat] #- Can group channels for video/audio/data
1a84e273 [deepseek-chat] #
1a84e273 [deepseek-chat] #• For your video application:*
1a84e274 [deepseek-chat] #- Place frame buffer in SRAM
1a84e274 [deepseek-chat] #- Ensure 32-bit alignment for DMA
1a84e274 [deepseek-chat] #- Consider placing other buffers in different cache "ways" if performance critical
1a84e274 [deepseek-chat] #
1a84e274 [deepseek-chat] #• No hardware banks*, but you can manually organize memory for optimal DMA/cache
1a84e274 [deepseek-chat] #performance. The unified SRAM simplifies programming but requires thoughtful layout for
1a84e274 [deepseek-chat] #high-bandwidth applications like video.
