1a8ddfe3 [deepseek-chat] #Yes, Schmitt triggers would help for PS/2 GPIO inputs. Here's why:
1a8ddfe3 [deepseek-chat] #
1a8ddfe3 [deepseek-chat] #• Benefits:*
1a8ddfe3 [deepseek-chat] #- Noise immunity: PS/2 uses open-collector with pull-ups, so signals can have slow edges.
1a8ddfe3 [deepseek-chat] #Schmitt triggers provide hysteresis, cleaning up marginal transitions.
1a8ddfe3 [deepseek-chat] #- Debouncing: Helps with contact bounce from mechanical switches (keyboards).
1a8ddfe4 [deepseek-chat] #- Signal integrity: Important with longer cables or noisy environments.
1a8ddfe4 [deepseek-chat] #
1a8ddfe4 [deepseek-chat] #• Pico GPIO Capabilities:*
1a8ddfe4 [deepseek-chat] #- RP2040 GPIOs have programmable Schmitt triggers (enabled by default on most pins)
1a8ddfe4 [deepseek-chat] #- Controlled via `padsbank0` registers
1a8ddfe4 [deepseek-chat] #- Can be enabled/disabled per pin
1a8ddfe4 [deepseek-chat] #
1a8ddfe4 [deepseek-chat] #• Implementation:*
1a8ddfe4 [deepseek-chat] #
1a8ddfe4 [deepseek-chat] #// Enable Schmitt trigger on a pin
1a8ddfe4 [deepseek-chat] #gpio_set_input_hysteresis_enabled(pin, true);
1a8ddfe4 [deepseek-chat] #
1a8ddfe4 [deepseek-chat] #
1a8ddfe4 [deepseek-chat] #• Considerations:*
1a8ddfe4 [deepseek-chat] #1. Default state: Schmitt triggers are usually enabled on RP2040, but verify for your
1a8ddfe4 [deepseek-chat] #specific pins
1a8ddfe4 [deepseek-chat] #2. Power consumption: Slightly higher with hysteresis enabled
1a8ddfe4 [deepseek-chat] #3. Speed trade-off: Schmitt triggers add small propagation delay (~ns), negligible for PS/2
1a8ddfe4 [deepseek-chat] #speeds
1a8ddfe4 [deepseek-chat] #4. PS/2 specific: The clock line especially benefits since devices generate the clock
1a8ddfe4 [deepseek-chat] #
1a8ddfe4 [deepseek-chat] #• Alternative/Complementary:*
1a8ddfe5 [deepseek-chat] #- Software debouncing still needed for key bounce
1a8ddfe5 [deepseek-chat] #- PIO can add sample delays to avoid glitches
1a8ddfe5 [deepseek-chat] #- External RC filter if signal particularly noisy
1a8ddfe5 [deepseek-chat] #
1a8ddfe5 [deepseek-chat] #For PS/2, enabling Schmitt triggers is recommended practice. The RP2040's built-in hysteresis
1a8ddfe5 [deepseek-chat] #should be sufficient for most applications.
1a8ddfe5 [deepseek-chat] #
