1a8df83a [deepseek-chat] #Good choice. Dedicated PIO state machine for PS/2 is clean. With your wiring:
1a8df83a [deepseek-chat] #
1a8df83a [deepseek-chat] #• GPIO Assignment:*
1a8df83a [deepseek-chat] #- GP0: PS/2 Data
1a8df83a [deepseek-chat] #- GP1: PS/2 Clock
1a8df83a [deepseek-chat] #- Both need pull-ups enabled (internal ~50kΩ should work)
1a8df83a [deepseek-chat] #
1a8df83a [deepseek-chat] #• PIO State Machine Design:*
1a8df83a [deepseek-chat] #- Clock pin as input, triggering on falling edges
1a8df83a [deepseek-chat] #- Data sampled on clock edges
1a8df83a [deepseek-chat] #- Shift in 11-bit frames (start + 8 data + parity + stop)
1a8df83a [deepseek-chat] #- Push complete bytes to FIFO when stop bit received
1a8df83b [deepseek-chat] #
1a8df83b [deepseek-chat] #• Advantages:*
1a8df83b [deepseek-chat] #- No CPU interrupts during bit reception
1a8df83b [deepseek-chat] #- PIO handles precise timing (≈60-100µs per bit)
1a8df83b [deepseek-chat] #- FIFO buffers keycodes for main loop polling
1a8df83b [deepseek-chat] #- Leaves CPU free for video/audio tasks
1a8df83b [deepseek-chat] #
1a8df83b [deepseek-chat] #• Implementation Outline:*
1a8df83b [deepseek-chat] #1. PIO waits for clock low (start bit)
1a8df83b [deepseek-chat] #2. Samples data bits on 8 clock cycles
1a8df83b [deepseek-chat] #3. Ignores parity/stop bits or validates them
1a8df83b [deepseek-chat] #4. Pushes data byte to FIFO
1a8df83b [deepseek-chat] #5. Returns to idle, watching for next start bit
1a8df83b [deepseek-chat] #
1a8df83b [deepseek-chat] #• Integration:*
1a8df83b [deepseek-chat] #- Poll PIO FIFO in main loop alongside video frame updates
1a8df83b [deepseek-chat] #- Simple queue for keycode processing
1a8df83b [deepseek-chat] #- Error recovery on timeout (missing stop bit)
1a8df83b [deepseek-chat] #
1a8df83b [deepseek-chat] #This approach matches your existing video/audio architecture well.
1a8df83b [deepseek-chat] #
