1a8f2779 [gemini-3.1-pro] #• 1. Should a keyboard work without any fuss?*
1a8f2779 [gemini-3.1-pro] #A PS/2 keyboard generally works without fuss because it defaults to sending scan codes immediately
1a8f2779 [gemini-3.1-pro] #upon power-up and key presses. A PS/2 mouse, however, does not. A mouse requires the host to send
1a8f2779 [gemini-3.1-pro] #an initialization command (`0xF4` Enable Data Reporting) before it will transmit any movement or
1a8f2779 [gemini-3.1-pro] #button data. Because your current `ps2.pio` program is strictly configured for receiving (RX), it
1a8f2779 [gemini-3.1-pro] #cannot send the required activation command to the mouse.
