1a8f9710 [roha] [GEMINI] result {"response":{"candidates":[{"content":{"parts":[{"text":"I have reviewed the tool calling logic. The infinite loop occurs because Gemini is not receiving the tool execution results in the format it expects, which prompts it to repeat the identical tool request. \n\nThere are three specific areas contributing to this in the code:\n\n1. **In `relay()`**: The tool execution results are being pushed to `rohaHistory` using `role: \"system\"` instead of `role: \"tool\"`. Because of this, the model processes the result as a general system instruction rather than the direct answer to its tool call.\n2. **In `prepareGeminiPrompt()`**: The `case \"tool\"` block is currently commented out. Even if the history had the correct role, the adapter drops the tool response before it reaches Gemini.\n3. **In `prepareGeminiPrompt()`**: The `case \"assistant\"` block also has the `item.tool_calls` handling commented out. Gemini's API strictly requires the conversation history to include the model's original `functionCall` immediately preceding the user's `functionResponse`.\n\nWould you like me to provide the specific code adjustments for these functions?","thoughtSignature":""}],"role":"model"},"finishReason":"STOP","index":0}],"usageMetadata":{"promptTokenCount":47264,"candidatesTokenCount":235,"totalTokenCount":50034,"promptTokensDetails":[{"modality":"TEXT","tokenCount":47264}],"thoughtsTokenCount":2535},"modelVersion":"gemini-3.1-pro-preview","responseId":"cDPKaeWcHcLu4-EPt5fd4A8"}}
