1a8ff591 [gemini-3.1-pro] #Thank you for sharing the updated code. The integration of the Google API (`@google/generative-ai`)
1a8ff591 [gemini-3.1-pro] #is well-structured and effectively bridges the OpenAI-style interface with Gemini's requirements.
1a8ff591 [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1a8ff591 [gemini-3.1-pro] #Here is a brief review of the Google API implementation:
1a8ff591 [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1a8ff591 [gemini-3.1-pro] #1. Prompt Preparation (`prepareGeminiPrompt`):
1a8ff591 [gemini-3.1-pro] #   - The mapping of roles (`system` to `system_instruction`, `user`, `model`, and `function`) is
1a8ff591 [gemini-3.1-pro] #correctly implemented.
1a8ff591 [gemini-3.1-pro] #   - Handling of multimodal inputs via `inlineData` for images is spot on.
1a8ff592 [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1a8ff592 [gemini-3.1-pro] #2. Tool Calling (`geminiTools` & `connectGoogle`):
1a8ff592 [gemini-3.1-pro] #   - Translating OpenAI tool schemas into Gemini's `functionDeclarations` is cleanly handled.
1a8ff592 [gemini-3.1-pro] #   - Potential Risk: In `connectGoogle`, calling `await result.response.text()` can
1a8ff592 [gemini-3.1-pro] #sometimes throw an error if the model returns only a function call without any accompanying
1a8ff592 [gemini-3.1-pro] #text. You might want to check for the presence of text parts before invoking the method.
1a8ff592 [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1a8ff592 [gemini-3.1-pro] #3. Text-to-Speech (`geminiSay` & `saveGeminiSpeech`):
1a8ff592 [gemini-3.1-pro] #   - Targeting the new `gemini-2.5-flash-preview-tts` model is a great addition.
1a8ff592 [gemini-3.1-pro] #   - Minor Note: In `saveGeminiSpeech`, your manual WAV header correctly sets the sample
1a8ff592 [gemini-3.1-pro] #rate to 24,000 Hz for the PCM codec, but the inline comment mentions `16kHz`. You may want to
1a8ff592 [gemini-3.1-pro] #update the comment for clarity.
1a8ff592 [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1a8ff592 [gemini-3.1-pro] #Overall, the changes look solid and maintain the consistency of your fountain architecture. Let me
1a8ff592 [gemini-3.1-pro] #know if you would like me to draft any specific adjustments for the text extraction or error
1a8ff592 [gemini-3.1-pro] #handling!
