1a90817f [gemini-3.1-pro] #1. UTF-8 Chunk Splitting: In `processUtf8`, if a multi-byte character sequence is split
1a90817f [gemini-3.1-pro] #across sequential `reader.read()` chunks, the `i + bytesNeeded <= value.length` check will fail. It
1a90817f [gemini-3.1-pro] #currently falls through to single-byte handling, which will corrupt the character. Buffering
1a90817f [gemini-3.1-pro] #incomplete sequences between reads would resolve this.
1a90817f [gemini-3.1-pro] #2. Timer Accumulation: Inside the `slopPrompt` `while` loop, `timerPromise` creates a new
1a90817f [gemini-3.1-pro] #`setTimeout` on every iteration. Because unresolved timeouts are not cleared when another promise
1a90817f [gemini-3.1-pro] #wins the race, this will accumulate pending timers and bloat the event loop.
1a90817f [gemini-3.1-pro] #3. Connection Cleanup: When a socket throws an error in `slopPrompt`'s race resolution,
1a90817f [gemini-3.1-pro] #`delete slopConnections[name]` is called, but the socket itself is not explicitly closed. This
1a90817f [gemini-3.1-pro] #could leave file descriptors open.
1a90817f [gemini-3.1-pro] #
1a90817f [gemini-3.1-pro] #Your grapheme segmentation and terminal width calculations are very robust. Please let me know if
